# todo-go

todo-go is a simple command-line todo list application written in Go. It allows users to manage their tasks through a set of easy-to-use commands.

## Features

- Add new tasks
- Remove tasks
- Toggle task completion status
- List all tasks
- Clear all tasks
- Persistent storage using CSV file

## Installation

1. Ensure you have Go 1.22.5 or later installed on your system.
2. Clone this repository:
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/todo-go.git
   ```
3. Navigate to the project directory:
   ```
   cd todo-go
   ```
4. Build the application:
   ```
   go build
   ```
5. Run application
   ```
   ./main
   ```
